<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Minister Conferred Highest Rank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today conferred on Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev the rank of
Federal Marshal, the highest military honor.
</P>
<P>
Conferring the honor on Sergeyev at the presidential residence
outside Moscow, Yeltsin had told Sergeyev he was happy with the
performance of the defense minister.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev, 59, the former commander of the strategic missile
force, was named defense minister by Yeltsin in May.
</P>
<P>
He is the first commander to receive this title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
