<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Ruling Coalition Endorses Formation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of all 14
component parties of Malaysia's ruling National Front today
endorsed the formation of the proposed National Economic Action
Council (NEAC) for helping the government solve present economic
problems.
</P>
<P>
The endorsement was given at a special meeting of the National
Front Supreme Council chaired by its chairman Mahathir Mohamad
here today.
</P>
<P>
The NEAC was proposed by the ruling party United Malays
National Organization (UMNO) led by Mahathir at an UMNO Supreme
Council meeting Thursday night and it will be established next
month.
</P>
<P>
The proposed NEAC will function as an advisory body to the
government on the measures needed to be taken to overcome the
effects on the economy following the fall in the value of the
Malaysian currency ringgit and the stock market, Prime Minister
Mahathir told reporters after today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said that the NEAC would include cabinet ministers involved
in economic matters as well as professionals in the field. The
council would not take on the role of the cabinet, but the two
would cooperate with each other, he added.
</P>
<P>
"All the leaders have pledged to take action to overcome the
effects on the national economy arising from the ringgit
depreciation and the fall in the stock market," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the setting up of the NEAC would enable the government
to take immediate action with the powers entrusted to it by the
cabinet while the ministries would implement the decisions made by
the council.
</P>
<P>
The NEAC would report to the cabinet from time to time,
Mahathir said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
