<HEADLINE> Romario Sidelined by Ranieri for a League Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Valencia coach Claudio Ranieri
on Friday sidelined Brazilian super star Romario from the line-up
for this weekend's league match with Atletico Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Romario said earlier in the week that he wanted to go back
home in a bid to secure a place in the Brazilian World Cup
squad.
</P>
<P>
Ranieri responded by saying that he will not do anything to
stop the striker if he leaves.
</P>
<P>
Romario joined Valencia last summer, but quickly went back
to Brazil on loan to Flamengo. Flamengo officials quoted in the
Spanish press have said Romario is unlikely to return to the
club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
