<HEADLINE> Vietnam Outlines Economic Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan
Van Khai today unveiled his government measures to solve the
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national assembly session, the prime minister said
the country's economy will continue the momentum of growth, but at
a lower speed.
</P>
<P>
He promised that the government will work hard to increase the
efficiency and competitiveness of the economy, quicken the pace of
the reform of state-owned enterprises, restructure the financial
system, and protect the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
