<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Warns Against Students Demonstrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Education, Sports
and Culture Minister Gabriel Machinga today warned pupils
throughout the country that the government will take stern
measures against students demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
Machinga, who was touring a former army establishment in
Nyajena in southern Zimbabwe which will soon be converted into a
secondary school, said pupils should concentrate on their school
work rather than resort to violence.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to be very strict with student who engage in
demonstrations," he said. They forget they are primarily at school to
learn, he added.
</P>
<P>
His warning came in the wake of violent demonstrations by
students countrywide who destroyed property worth of hundreds of
thousands of dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
