<HEADLINE> PNA Urges Israel to Stop Settlement Activities in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian chief peace
negotiator Saeb Erekat today urged Israel to stop the settlement
activities in the West Bank city of Hebron, reports reaching here
from the Gaza Strip said.
</P>
<P>
In a note sent to the Israeli negotiation team, the Palestinian
official said Israel's violation of the signed peace accords, the
kidnaping of the Palestinian civilians and settlement activities
in Hebron will lead to the undermining of the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Erekat asked Israel to release two Palestinian youths and two
soldiers detained by the Israeli forces in the West Bank recently.
</P>
<P>
He also called on Israel to set free Ataf Alayan, a female
Palestinian prisoner who was rearrested by the Israeli police last
month after she was released several months ago from Israeli
prison under the Oslo accords signed by Israel and the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
Alayan went on a hunger strike to protest against the arrest
and her detention without charge by Israel. Her hunger strike has
entered the fourth week.
</P>
<P>
In his note, Erekat condemned the Israeli decision to expand
the settlement activities in Hebron and deemed it a grave
violation of the agreement signed by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Erekat has earlier sent a similar note to the office of Israeli
Foreign Minister David Levy. 
