<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Calls for Restraint on Burundi-Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The central organ of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention Management and Resolution today expressed its concern
over the tension on the Burundi-Tanzanian border and appealed for
restraint from all parties.
</P>
<P>
It also called for the urgent resumption of the Arusha
negotiation process under the facilitation of former Tanzanian
President Mwalimu Julius Nyerere on the basis of the decisions of
the September regional summit held in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
The call was contained in a communique adopted at the end of
the seventh ordinary session of the central organ at the
ministerial level in Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
The communique requested countries of the region to continue
to regularly reassess the impact of the sanctions against Burundi
and to act under the decisions by the fifth Dar es Salaam
regional summit.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in the Comoros, it reiterated its unflinching
commitment to the unity and territorial integrity of the Comoros
and its determination to do everything in its power to contribute
to ensuring respect for the cardinal OAU principle.
</P>
<P>
It declared as null and void the outcome of the referendum for
self-determination organized in Anjouan on October 26 and invited
the rest of the international community to do so.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the crisis in Sierra Leone, the central organ
reiterated its condemnation of the coup d'etat and repeated its
call for the reinstatement of the legitimate government of
president Tejan Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
It urged the military junta to fulfill its obligations under
the Conakry peace accord it signed with the west African
peace-keeping force.
</P>
<P>
The communique also expresed its concern with the situation in
Somalia. It called on all Somali factions to make a determinded
effort to bring intra and inter-clan aggression to an end and
further appealed to them to cooperate with the efforts being
deployed the OAU and other world organizations in the search of a
solution to the crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
On the various initiatives aimed at enhancing Africa's
capacity in peace support operation, the central organ affirmed
Africa's determination to assume its responsibility for peace,
security and stability on the continent within the framework of
the charters of OAU and the United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
