<HEADLINE> Pro-Israeli Army Warns Israel Against Withdrawal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Pro-Israeli South Lebanese
Army (SLA) Commander Antoine Lahd said today that Israel will be
perceived as a "traitor" if it withdraws from Lebanon without
considering the needs of the people there.
</P>
<P>
The official Lebanese National News Agency reported that the
commander of the Israeli-backed militia made the warning in a
letter to Israeli opposition legislator Yossi Beilin, who is
leading a grass-root campaign for a unilateral withdrawal from
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
With mounting Israeli military casualties in south Lebanon
caused by resistance of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah guerrillas,
opposition to continuous occupation and calls for unconditional
withdrawal from south Lebanon is becoming stronger in Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The possible withdrawal from Lebanon cannot be considered an
internal Israeli issue, as it directly affects the future of the
area's inhabitants who have fought alongside with you," Lahd
wrote to Beilin.
</P>
<P>
"Israel will be perceived as a traitor," he added.
</P>
<P>
The SLA, with its 2,500 militiamen, is controlling Lebanon's
southern city of Jezzine which faces the 1,200-square-kilometer
buffer zone in south Lebanon which was set up by Israel in 1985 to
protect its northern towns from cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Israel has an estimated 2,000 soldiers in the so-called
"security zone." 
</P>
