<HEADLINE> UN Decides to Extend Mandate of UNDOF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the United Nations today decided to extend the mandate of the
United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for a period of six
months until May 31, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council made the decision after reviewing the
latest report on UNDOF by UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
In the report Annan said despite the present quiet situation in
the Israeli-Syrian sector, the situation in the Middle East
continued to be potentially dangerous and was likely to remain so,
unless and until a comprehensive settlement covering all aspects
of the Middle East problem could be reached.
</P>
<P>
In the report, the UN chief recommended to the Security Council
that the mandate of UNDOF be extended for six months.
</P>
<P>
UNDOF was established in 1974. Its present mandate expires on
November 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
