<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Tea Wins World Quality Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Tea
Production and Marketing Enterprise said today that it has won
the 1997 international Gold Star for Quality award.
</P>
<P>
Deresse Kassu, general manager of the enterprise, told local
newsmen that the award was given by Business Initiative
Direction, an international organization entrusted with the task
of encouraging the quality of industrial and agricultural
productions, recently in a special ceremony held in Madrid,
Spain.
</P>
<P>
A total of 133 countries had competed for the award, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Kassu, Ethiopia, which became self-sufficient in
tea production in 1988/89, has exported about 1,500-2,000 tons of
high-land tea since 1994/95. 
</P>
</TEXT>
