<HEADLINE> Lufthansa Eyes Alliance with Singapore Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Germany's national airline
Lufthansa is on the course to forge an alliance with Singapore
Airlines to boost its business in Asia, German news reports said
today.
</P>
<P>
The German news agency DPA today quoted officials of the German
Federal Cartel Office as saying that Lufthansa had requested a
meeting with the office to discuss a "bilateral alliance" with
Singapore Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Lufthansa today declined to comment on the reports, with a
company spokesman only saying that Lufthansa was planned to
disclose "something very significant" at a press conference in
Singapore on November 24.
</P>
<P>
According to German newspaper reports, Lufthansa and Singapore
Airlines would cooperate bilaterally for the time being. It had
not been discussed for the moment whether the Singapore carrier
would join the multilateral "Star Alliance", which links Lufthansa
with United Airlines of the United States, the SAS Scandinavian
Airlines System, Air Canada, Varig and Thai Airways.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some industry analysts reportedly said that the
alliance between Lufthansa and Singapore Airlines, and its
possible link with the "Star Alliance" would put a question mark
on the German airline's current cooperation with Thai Airways as
well as Singapore Airlines' cooperation with the U.S. Delta Air
Lines and Swissair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
