<HEADLINE> Belgium to Interrogate Father-Daughter Murder Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Public prosecutors are
scheduled to interrogate on Saturday the daughter of the
Hungarian-born pastor who was charged with murdering six members
of his family.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine-year-old Agnes Pandy, arrested late Thursday in
Brussels, was charged with committing murder or aiding in murder,
local television RTBF quoted prosecutors as saying.
</P>
<P>
The father, Andras Pandy who was arrested last month after
human bones had been dug out from inside his houses, will also be
interrogated alongside his daughter Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The protestant priest was charged with murdering his two former
wives and four of his eight children. The six members of the
pastor family disappeared between 1986 and 1989.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said that the human bones found in the pastor's
houses belonged to different human beings.
</P>
<P>
Though neighbors and a Dutch priest reported to local
authorities about the unaccounted disappearance of the family
members, Pandy explained that the disappeared family members had
gone back to Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
