<HEADLINE> Japanese PM to Visit Canada After APEC Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister
Ryutaro Hashimoto will make an official visit to Canada after the
APEC Economic Leaders Meeting here, the Canadian government has
announced.
</P>
<P>
This will be Hashimoto's first official visit to Canada in his
capacity as prime minister of Japan, and the first visit by a
Japanese prime minister since 1989.
</P>
<P>
"It will be an excellent opportunity to follow through on our
mutual commitment to building closer relations," Canadian Prime
Minister Jean Chretien said while making the announcement.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers will discuss commitments agreed to last
year in the Canada-Japan Agenda for Cooperation, according to the
Canadian government.
</P>
<P>
Japan is Canada's second largest trading partner after the
United States. Two-way trade reached a record 24 billion Canadian
dollars in 1995. This dropped slightly last year to about 22
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is a key source of both direct and portfolio investment in
Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
