<HEADLINE> Chretien Views Jiang's Visit to Canada Chance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin's state visit to Canada will be "an excellent
opportunity" to advance the relations between Canada and China,
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien said today.
</P>
<P>
Chretien announced that Jiang's visit, which will take place
following the informal meeting the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum leaders, will include events in Calgary,
Ottawa and Toronto.
</P>
<P>
"President Jiang Zemin's visit to Canada is an excellent
opportunity to advance the special relationship that exist between
Canada and China and the important commercial ties we share,"
Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
"Since our first Team Canada trade mission to China in 1994, it
has been gratifying to witness the growing presence of Canadian
firms within the China market," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to strengthening the friendship between our
countries and working together to further our common interests as
Pacific partners," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is due to arrive here to attend APEC meeting Sunday,
will receive an official welcome from Governor General Rumeo Le
Branc in Calgary on November 26.
</P>
<P>
As Canada's fifth largest export market, China is a priority
market for Canadian exporters.
</P>
<P>
Launched in 1996, Canada's trade action plan for China and
China's Hong Kong aims to reach 18 billion U.S. dollars in two-way
trade by 2000. The trade between the two grew about 35 percent
over five years, reaching about 5.8 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also have cooperation in other areas
including environment and peace and security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
