<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Awards Defense Minister Marshal Rank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
read out a decree awarding Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev the rank
of marshal today in the Rus residence, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The president had talks with the defense minister and gave
Sergeyev the highest rank of the Russian army to show approval of
his work.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev told President Yeltsin in detail about the situation
in the armed forces and implementation of the reform, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The two also discussed results of blending of the missile
troops, the aerospace force and the air defense troops,
transformation of the supreme command of the army, the air force
and the air defense troops, and plans of the Defense Ministry for
the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev was appointed defense minister on May 23 of the year.
He is the first military officer who has the rank of marshal in
the Russian Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
