<HEADLINE> Canada, Singapore Ink Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Canada and Singapore inked a
memorandum of understanding (MOU) on cooperation in information
and telecommunications technology here today.
</P>
<P>
"This MOU opens a technological gateway between our countries
that should act as a catalyst for increased scientific, business,
educational and cultural ties," said Canadian Minister for
International Trade Sergio Marchi.
</P>
<P>
"It is a milestone in our excellent bilateral relations," said
Lee Yock Suan, Singapore's second minister for finance.
</P>
<P>
"Close collaboration between our two countries in the fields of
information and communications technology will enhance our
competitive advantages in these strategic industries," Lee added.
</P>
<P>
The MOU will support the development of technologies, products
and services for the benefit of industry, education and research
in Canada and Singapore, according to the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Apart from signing the pact, the two officials also witnessed
the inking of 13 agreements estimated to be worth 150 million
Canadian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
