<HEADLINE> Kuwait: Gulf Summit to Be Held on Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait said today that
the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) Summit scheduled on December
20 to 22 in Kuwait will be convened on time.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Finance
Minister Nasser Abdullah Al-Roudhan in response to a local media
report that the summit has been postponed. He stressed that the
conference will be convened as it is planned.
</P>
<P>
A preparatory meeting attended by the GCC foreign ministers
will be held here on November 25-26.
</P>
<P>
GCC, a regional economic and defense organization founded in
1981, groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates,
Oman, Bahrain and Qatar. 
</P>
