<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ruby Defends her Second Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, November 22 (Xinhua) -- France's Karine Ruby defended
her title of the snowboard World Cup giant slalom crown with her
second victory of the season in Kaprun, Austria, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ruby, who won last week's opening giant slalom in Tignes,
France, clocked an overall time of one minute 56.56 seconds to
leave her closest rival, Italy's Margerita Parini, 1.78 seconds
behind.
</P>
<P>
American giant slalom world champion Sondra van Ert was 2.36
seconds adrift, finishing third.
</P>
<P>
Ruby now has 25 career giant slalom wins, confirming her status
as a gold medal contender at next February's Winter Olympics in
Nagano where the snowboard disciplines of giant slalom and
halfpipe make their Games debut.  
</P>
</TEXT>
