<HEADLINE> South Korea Dominates Tenth Asian Archery Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 22 (Xinhua) -- South Korea remained
at pole position in both the men's and women's events on the
second day of the 10th Asian Archery Tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The top four slots all went to South Koreans in the women's
50m/30m event with two-time world junior champion Kang Hyun Ji
snatching the title with 1,336 points.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Olympics gold medallist Yun Hye Young followed with
1,330 points, in front of Chung Chang Sook, 1,326, and Hwang Jin
Hae, 1,308.
</P>
<P>
In the women's team event, South Korea grabbed the first spot
with a total of 3,992 points ahead of China, 3,878, and Chinese
Taipei 3,809.
</P>
<P>
In the men's individual competition, South Korea's Oh Kyo Moon
took the lead with 1,336 points. His compatriots Kim Bo
Ram collected 1,326 and Hong Sung Chil accumulated 1,307.
</P>
<P>
South Korea led the men's 50m/30m team event with 3,969 points
while in second position was Japan with 3,816 and Chinese Taipei
 third with 3,802 points. 
