<HEADLINE> Central China to Become Rising Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, November 22 (Xinhua) -- A three-day seminar on
development in central China oriented to the 21st century closed
today in Wuhan, capital of Central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Over 140 experts and economists from some leading government
departments including the State Planning Commission and the
Chinese Academy of Social Sciences put forward many valuable
suggestions on speeding up economic development in central China.
</P>
<P>
Central China embraces Henan, Anhui, Hubei, Hunan and Jiangxi
provinces, which cover nine percent of the total area and a
quarter of the farmland of the country. Its output of farm produce
accounts for one third of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the region is a leading base of raw materials, water
energy and 25 mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
Experts deem that central China should fully tap its potentials
and build a closer, coordinated relationship among them with the
aim to become a fast growing economic zone at the turn of the
century. They suggested that the central government adopt
preferential policies towards the central part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
