<HEADLINE> Tour of Italy to Open in Nice Next May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The Tour of Italy will kick off
with a time trial prologue in Nice, France next May, marking the
cycling race starts on foreign soil for just the fifth time,
organizers announced in Milan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 22 stages of the 81st edition will cover a total of 3,830
kilometers to the finish in Milan. The race will start on May 16
with the 6-kilometer prologue and wind up on June 7 with no rest
days in between.
</P>
<P>
There are two individual time trials, of 34 and 38 kilometers (21
and 23.5 miles).
</P>
<P>
It is a relatively flat course, with fewer tough mountain
passes than in the past. The highest climb will be to the top of
Passo Sella, at 2,214 meters (7,306 feet) above sea level, during
the 17th stage, from Asiago to Selva Gardena.
</P>
<P>
Up to 20 teams, with nine riders each, will be allowed to
compete for the 2.5 billion lire (dlrs 1.5 million) in total prize
money.
</P>
<P>
Ivan Gotti won the 1997 Giro, the first Italian to capture the
prestigious race since Franco Chioccioli in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
