<HEADLINE> Pension Rise for Gorkha Ex-servicemen Likely: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Foreign Minister
Kamal Thapa said today that positive progress has been made in
talks with India and Britain over pension rise for the Gorkha
ex-servicemen.
</P>
<P>
The official RSS news agency quoted Thapa as saying that talks
have been held at various levels with the Indian and British
governments about increasing the remuneration, pensions and other
facilities of the Gorkha ex-servicemen.
</P>
<P>
Thapa told the press here that remuneration and some facilities
have been increased for the ex-servicemen and talks are now
focusing on the pension issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that Nepalese are engaged in Indian and British armies
under a trilateral treaty signed between Nepal, India and Britain
in 1947, but they are receiving lower remuneration, pensions and
other facilities compared with their Indian and British
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The Nepalese serving in Indian and British armies are called
the Gorkha soldiers.  
