<HEADLINE> Shanghai Enterprises Donates 1.6 Million Yuan to Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Some 10,000 Shanghai
enterprises have donated over 1.58 million yuan to Project Hope, a
nongovernmental program which supports school children from
poverty-stricken families.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch of Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
(ICBC), which acts as the agent for over 10,000 corporate donors,
has transferred the donation to the China Youth Development
Foundation, the project organizer.
</P>
<P>
The donations came from medium- to large-sized state-owned
enterprises, private plants and individuals, as well as 587
affiliate savings banks of the ICBC Shanghai branch.
</P>
<P>
Corporations in the city have been encouraged to donate at
least 100 yuan each to the project in order to facilitate the
development of education in poverty-stricken regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
