<HEADLINE> Bonilla Retain WBA Flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Jose Bonilla of Venezuela retain
his World Boxing Association (WBA) flyweight title by beating
Japan's Keiji Yamaguchi with a technical knockout in Osaka, Japan,
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Referee stopped the bout two minutes 20 seconds into the sixth
round when Bonilla unleashed an array of punches to corner the
Japanese.
</P>
<P>
Several seconds earlier in the round, Bonilla fired a left hook
to the face to floor Yamaguchi, scoring the first down in the
match.
</P>
<P>
It was Bonilla's third defence of the title he grabbed from
Saen Sor-Ploenchit of Thailand in November 1996, boosting his
record to 24 wins, including 12 KOs, against three defeats.
</P>
<P>
Yamaguchi once became the WBA junior flyweight champion in May
1996 and lost in his second defence of the title seven months
later. It was his fifth world title match with his record reducing
to 22 wins, including eight KOs, and three defeats. 
</P>
