<HEADLINE> World Bank Loans to Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has granted loans
of over 279 million US dollars for agricultural development in
east China's Shandong Province, accounting for 15 percent of the
total foreign funds the province has used for related projects.
</P>
<P>
The six projects funded by World Bank loans are mainly located
in economically disadvantaged northwestern parts of the province
and in poverty-stricken areas in the Yimeng Mountains. Related
projects cover agriculture, water control, animal husbandry,
processing of agricultural products, aquatics breeding, and the
development of selected coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
The eight medium- to large-sized irrigation projects currently
in operation have greatly improved low or medium-yield land
covering 500,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
World Bank loans have helped to establish 21 processing
enterprises in Yimeng's animal husbandry sector, and have provided
jobs for 66,000 local women. 
</P>
