<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A grenade was thrown Friday night at the house
occupied by Jewish settlers in East Jerusalem's Ras Amud Arab
neighborhood, but no one was hurt, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the attack, and Israeli
police have not made any arrests yet.
</P>
<P>
The attack came after the Wednesday night's shooting attack
against two Jewish religious students near the Damascus Gate in
the Muslim Quarter of the Old City. One of the students was killed
and the other seriously injured by automatic rifle fired by
unknown Muslim militant. (Jerusalem-Settlers-Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The German and French ambassadors to Iran returned
to their posts this morning, marking the end of a seven-month
diplomatic crisis between Iran and the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
German ambassador Horst Baechmann and French ambassador
Jean-Pierre Masset arrived here on a Lufthansa flight from
Frankfurt. They were the last two of EU envoys to resume their
missions in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Other EU envoys were back in town November 14, one day after
Iran reached a compromise with the EU by announcing to accept a
proposal of EU rotating Chairman, Luxembourg Foreign Minister
Jacques Poos. (Iran-EU-Ambassadors)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam apologized
Saturday to the people for the nation' economic problems and
pleaded for collective cooperation to overcome the crisis.
</P>
<P>
In his nationwide-televised address, the President asked the
people to join forces with the government's efforts to overcome
the present economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive admitted that the dazzling development over
the past 30 years had also given birth to structural problems in
the nation's economy. (SKorea-Economic-Crisis)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Torrential rains killed seven people in several
Ugandan districts, ''The New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
In eastern Iganga District, a baby died instantly when a hut in
Bugiri collapsed, and his mother was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Another resident in the same district was drowned when he tried
to cross the river of Malaba on the way from Kenya to to his home
in Amoni-Kakineyi. (Uganda-Rains) 
</P>
