<HEADLINE> Novotna, Spirlea Through to Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Jana Novotna of
the Czech Republic and eighth seed Irina Spirlea of Romania
survived three-set matches to reach the semi-finals of the Chase
Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Czech, the only surviver of the top six seeds in the
event, beat Spaniard Atantxa Sanchez Vicario 6-4, 3-6, 6-1, while
the Romanian outlasted 11-seeded Mary Joe Fernandez 5-7, 6-2, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
World number 3 Novotna will take up Spirlea in her ninth
consecutive season-ending event.
</P>
<P>
Novotna broke twice at 3-1 and 5-1 in the final set, thanks to
a combination of backhand errors and double-faults of the
Spaniard, who had won none titles this season.
</P>
<P>
Novotna clung to the only match point of the game to dump
Sanchez, the third-time Grand Slam titlist.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez apparently had the better of the game when she
created three match points at 5-4.
</P>
<P>
But Spirlea, who had never let the Spaniard win a single set
before the clash, held up in the exciting 10th game and rallied
on two break points.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez saved one break point but surrendered the game when
she sent a forehand out.
</P>
<P>
The other semi-final matches will be played between two French
players seventh seed Mary Pierce and Nathalie Tauziat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
