<HEADLINE> Mbeki Calls for Putting Into Full Use of African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 22 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki appealed the people in Africa to put into
full use of the continent's rich natural resources to speed up
its economic emancipation.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki made the appeal Friday at the opening ceremony of the
United Nations Economic Commission's second regional conference
of African Ministers responsible for the development and
utilization of minerals and energy resources.
</P>
<P>
He said it is Africa's natural resources and varied sources of
energy which served as the main catalyst for the integration of
Africa. in the history of world.
</P>
<P>
But the tragedy of the past is that the European scramble for
African natural resources, which had accelerated the development
of Europe and bring the African continent to a state of under-
development.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki urged the two-day conference in Durban of South Africa
to focus its discussions on how Africa develop and put into full
use of its rich resources to put the continent on the road to
renewal, prosperity and peace.
</P>
<P>
"What is not in doubt is that despite the many decades of
exploitation of these natural resources, vast amounts still
remain either unexplored, badly merchandised, or their value
completely lost to most of us."
</P>
<P>
Africa should seek social and economic emancipation in a world
characterized by the universal impact of the revolution in
science and technology and the globalization of all economic
activity, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
