<HEADLINE> Theatrical Festival Planned for Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- China will hold a theatrical
festival for students in primary and secondary schools to enrich
their extracurricular activities.
</P>
<P>
The theatrical festival will be jointly organized by the State
Education Commission, the Ministry of Culture, the Ministry of
Radio, Film and Television and the central committee of the
Communist Youth League.
</P>
<P>
Theatrical performances are planned for all the municipalities,
provinces and autonomous regions of China. Local education
commissions will recommend programs to the organizing committee of
the festival which will select a few to be performed on the final
evening in Beijing, according to a news briefing held in the Great
Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee has chosen 80 songs for the festival
from 3,000 pieces written specifically for the students by
professional and amateur composers as well as teachers and
students.
</P>
<P>
The State Education Commission has taken 10 measures to shift
the current education system from examination-oriented education
to quality education, an official said.
</P>
<P>
"The festival is just one measure taken to encourage the
development of quality education in the primary and secondary
schools," the organizing committee official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
