<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Claim Seven in Ugandan Districts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains killed seven
people in several Ugandan districts, ''The New Vision'' reported
today.
</P>
<P>
In eastern Iganga District, a baby died instantly when a hut
in Bugiri collapsed, and his mother was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Another resident in the same district was drowned when he
tried to cross the river of Malaba on the way from Kenya to to
his home in Amoni-Kakineyi.
</P>
<P>
Busia District Council Chairman Edward Wabudi said that
Okame-Kisole River burst its banks and one villager was drowned
in the flood waters.
</P>
<P>
In central Nakasongola District, Kamuwanula Primary School
block collapsed in rain and three pupils were injured.
</P>
<P>
In western Kabarole District, hundred travellers were stranded
on the way from Fort Portal to Mubende during heavy rain which
made the road impassable.
</P>
<P>
Agricutural officials warned that thousands of acres of food
crops are submerged in water and it could cause food shortage in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
