<HEADLINE> 3 Killed as Quake Rocks Chittagong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 22 (Xinhua) -- At least three persons were
killed, over 300 injured and 24 others missing in Chittagong when
an earthquake shook the whole of Bangladesh Friday, official
sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The quake rocked the entire country between 5:20 and 5:35 p.m.
Friday, the Dhaka Met Office said, the epicenter of the earthquake
was located at 247 kilometers northeast of Chittagong and this was
the second quake in the month that rocked the country after first
one on November 10.
</P>
<P>
The strength of the tremor could not be measured as there was
no quake measuring implement in the country, and there is only one
seismological observatory in Chittagong, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The tremor also shook Dhaka, Munshiganj, Tangail, Jessore,
Chandpur, Rangpur, Bhola, Sandwip, Sitakunda, Rangamati, Cos's
Bazar, Barisal, Sylhet and Jhenidah, the Met office said.
</P>
<P>
A newly-constructed five-storey building collapsed and many
other buildings in Chittagong developed cracks or get tilted, the
sources stated.
</P>
<P>
Fire brigade and police rushed to the quake-hit places soon,
and many injured persons were rushed to the Chittagong Medical
College Hospital, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
