<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Considers to Form Cooperative Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
now actively considering formation of a cooperative council to
make the system more dynamic and potential through amending
cooperatives rules.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Minister of Local Government Rural
Development and Cooperatives Zillur Rahman while inaugurating the
37th annual conference of the Christian cooperative Credit Union
Limited in Dhaka Friday.
</P>
<P>
local press reports today quoted the minister as saying that
"the proposed council will be formed comprising leaders and
representatives of different organizations and cooperative
societies of various professionals."
</P>
<P>
The minister said a number of development projects like
artisan, pottery, cottage industry, poultry farming would be
raised under the forthcoming five-year plan.
</P>
<P>
Massive schemes are being taken through cooperative system for
alleviation of poverty, creation of employment opportunity for
both rural and urban areas particularly for women cooperators, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that as the country is mainly dependent on
agriculture, it is going to attain self-sufficiency in food, and
its peasantry should be inspired to apply modern technology
through cooperatives to achieve prime objective of economic
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The government had already procured two billion taka (about
44.64 million U.S. dollars) for a project for marketization of
local agri-products through the cooperative system, he stated.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that in a developing country like Bangladesh,
there is no alternative to an organized and effective cooperative
system for eradicating poverty of the people in an abject poverty.
</P>
<P>
Without cooperative movement, there is no other means for
farmers, laborers and other working people to change their
destiny, he stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
