<DOCNO> XIE19971122.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Company Wins Hydro-Power Project Bid in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, November (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company's bid has been
accepted on a hydro-power project in Albania.
</P>
<P>
He Bing, General Manager of a company named, "China Hainan
Science, Industry and Trade Enterprises Corporation," and the
Albanian Economy and Privatization Deputy Minister Pajtim Bello
signed the bid agreement Thursday. The ministry has ratified the
agreement which will allow the Chinese company to build the power
plant in Bushat.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two sides will continue negotiations
until the final accord is reached next year.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the largest projects China has bid on
successfully. China will export equipment and technology to East
Europe that is valued at 150 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Other seven companies that bid on the project were from
Austria, Switzerland, Germany and Slovenia. The bidding on the
project began in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
