<HEADLINE> More Cholera Cases found in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 22 (Xinhua) -- More cholera cases have been
found in Sri Lanka since September, Health Ministry sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Epidemiological Unit of the ministry, out of
636 patients who were admitted to hospitals, 240 positive cases of
cholera had been detected from September 29 to November 21.
</P>
<P>
The cholera epidemic was first reported in Chilaw district in
the northwestern coast, 75 kilometers from Colombo, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva has already appointed a
Special Health Task Force to take immediate action to prevent the
disease from spreading, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
All private hospitals have been requested to transfer patients
with symptoms of cholera to state hospitals immediately.
</P>
<P>
Continuous heavy rains and the stagnation of rain water in
drains are considered the main cause for the spread of the
disease.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
