<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman Says China, UN to Cooperate on Human Right in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- China will cooperate with UN
in implementing human right covenants in Hong Kong, Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said here today.
</P>
<P>
China will provide relevant UN departments with the situation
of implementing the related stipulations of the two covenants,
namely, the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights
and the International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural
Rights, in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), in
order to enable them and the international community to have a
better understanding, Shen said in response to a correspondent's
question.
</P>
<P>
According to the Sino-British Joint Declaration and the Basic
Law of HKSAR, the spokesman said, the articles in the two
covenants that are suitable to Hong Kong will be in effect there
and will be implemented through HKSAR laws.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China will do so to give an expression to the
principle of "One Country, Two Systems", though the country is not
a signatory state to the two covenants yet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
