<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fundamentals Favor Long-term Growth of China's Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Economists at an international
seminar in south China say they agreed that the fundamentals are
good for the long-term development of the Chinese stock market.
</P>
<P>
Both the system of shareholders and the capital market in China
have developed rapidly in recent years and have played a positive
role in changes in funding, distribution of resources, the
operation of enterprises, and integrating the stock market of
China with those of the world according to the participants from
China, the U.S., Europe, Japan, the World Bank, and the IMF.
</P>
<P>
The endorsement of the shareholder system by the 15th Party
Congress in September will help its development and the capital
market, they said, noting that the stable growth of the Chinese
economy will support the long-term development of the stock
market, with annual economic growth estimated at 8 to 10 percent
in the years to come and inflation at less than five percent.
</P>
<P>
The indicators mean a favorable macro-economic environment for
the stock market and the listed companies.
</P>
<P>
The revised Criminal Law, which took effect in October, will
deter financial crimes and protect the rights and interests of
investors, which will in turn reduce risks at the marketplace and
attract more funds to the stock market.
</P>
<P>
However, economists say that the expansion of the stock market
must be met with increasing demand, or there will be slumps.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
