<HEADLINE> More Chinese Finding Jobs Through Personnel Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 22 (Xinhua) -- In Hebei Province, in
north China, 215,000 people found jobs by using personnel markets,
in 1996, according to the Provincial Market Building
Administration.
</P>
<P>
The personnel market business started in 1993 and there are now
158 personnel markets, and 11 major cities have organizations to
run the personnel markets.
</P>
<P>
Nine cities encourage enterprises to find employees through the
markets, and many cities encourage university graduates to look
for jobs by using them.
</P>
<P>
Between 1993 and 1996, the province held 13 personnel exchange
fairs, attracting over 500,000 visitors.
</P>
<P>
Many large and medium-sized enterprises and government offices
in charge of taxes, banking, and insurance also go to personnel
markets to recruit staff members.  
</P>
