<HEADLINE> Three Semi-final Berths Booked in Doubles Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Indian and American pairs
have claimed two other berths of semi-finals for the ATP World
Doubles Championships with defending "Woodies" favorite for the
last spot.
</P>
<P>
India's Mahesh Bhupathi and Leander Paes of Yellow Group and
Americans Rick Leach and Jonathan Stark in Green Group both
qualified in Friday's round-robin matches of the 500,000 U.S.
dollars tournament played in Harford, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The fifth-seeded Indians, who have won sixth titles this year,
beat American Trevor Kornemann and Australian David MacPherson
6-4, 7-6 (7-5), while the other qualifiers, seeded fourth, took
another straight-set win over compatriots Don Johnson and
Francisco Montana, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Dutch duo Jacco Eltingh and Paul Haarhuis had already booked
the spot as the leaders of Yellow Group.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Mark Woodforde and Todd Woodbridge, world
top doubles players, need a win for qualifying though they are
unbeaten in Green Group.
</P>
<P>
A win over Canada's Sebastien Lareau and American Alex O'Brien
will set up a clash for the two-time champions of the tournament
"Woodies" with the Indians on Saturday. 
