<DOCNO> XIE19971122.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sixty Animal Species in Danger of Extinction in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Some 60 animal species are
in danger of extinction in the Mexican southern state of Chiapas,
because of deforestation and other environmental depredations in
the state.
</P>
<P>
Data provided by the National History Institute show that
deforestation in Chiapas has resulted in the destruction of more
than 70 percent of the natural habitat of several animal species.
</P>
<P>
The institute's biodiversity conservation director Alberto
Guichard said that the loss of animal habitat is alarming, but
even more dangerous is the fact that the remaining 30 percent is
also threatened by forest fires, excessive lumbering and
over-exploitation of the soil.
</P>
<P>
The expert said that during the past 30 years, the habitat of
the nearly 60 extinct species has been turned into grazing and
agricultural land.
</P>
<P>
He said some species, such as the green parrot, or the jabiru,
have not been seen in the state in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
He added that species such as the harpy eagle, the tapir, the
jaguar, and small birds such as tangara, quetzal and pavon, are
also in grave danger of extinction.
</P>
<P>
Small species, such as salamanders and lizards, could also
vanish because of the destruction of their habitat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971122.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economic Reform Package Drafted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government's think
tank is stepping up drafting an economic reform package to be
implemented in 41 pilot cities across the country, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Included in the package are the reform of State-owned
enterprises, urban economic restructuring, housing and market
reforms and the establishment of a social security system.
</P>
<P>
According to Tong Daning, division chief of the Comprehensive
Programming and Experimentation Department with the State
Commission for Economic Restructuring, the reform measures are
designed to answer the question: what is the socialist market
economy?
</P>
<P>
Some large state-owned firms with a good economic performance
or large market potential are encouraged to form themselves into
group enterprises through merging or buying loss-making firms.
</P>
<P>
Such measures can help optimize the capital structure in
certain regions, said Tong.
</P>
<P>
The means of alleviating the debts of state-owned enterprises
and adjusting their debt structure is another important issue.
</P>
<P>
The State Commission for Economic Restructuring, together with
the State Economic and Trade Commission, are launching experiments
in some cities to find ways of solving the debt problems of
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
China selected 18 pilot cities to initiate its comprehensive
urban reform program in 1992. The number of cities was increased
to 39 last year, with Urumqi and Shihezi in the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region being added to the group this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971122.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austrian Minister Urges New Gun Laws After Recent Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Austria's Interior Minister
Karl Schloegl called for tough gun laws today shortly after the
country's worst shooting incident in many years.
</P>
<P>
"There is an urgent need for a tough, strict gun law and I will
be seeking a majority (vote for it) in parliament," he told state
television after a man shot and killed six people Thursday night
at Mauterndorf, a village about 100 kilometers south of Salzburg.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, an applicant for a gun license must
undergo an assessment to prove suitability to own a weapon, and
shotguns have to be registered with the local police.
</P>
<P>
Josef Gautsch, a 36-year-old unemployed machinist, committed
suicide when police caught up with him. Earlier he killed his
former wife, her new husband and their three-year-old daughter.
Other victims included the school master of the middle school
where he graduated and the deputy mayor of the village.
</P>
<P>
The motive for the shooting is still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
Villagers said Gautsch was a loner and familiar with guns.
Police found several weapons and a stack of ammunition in his flat.
</P>
<P>
The sale of pump action shotguns was banned in Austria in 1995
after a sharp increase in the number of murders committed with the
guns reported, many of them by teenagers who killed members of
their families.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, nearly 20 shooting cases between family members
have occurred.
</P>
<P>
Just two days ago, a 39-year-old official with the country's
Agriculture and Forestry Ministry killed his elder sister and
wounded his mother and brother in a dispute over the inheritance
of a vineyard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
