<HEADLINE> China to Host APEC Meetings in 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 21 (Xinhua) -- China will host the
meetings of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum in
2001, Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to announce here that the Chinese Government has
decided to host the APEC Meeting in 2001 as its contribution to
the economic cooperation in the Asia-Pacific," Qian told the 9th
ministerial meeting of APEC.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting, which started today, will be followed by
an informal meeting of APEC leaders next week.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking forward to meeting all APEC members in China at
the beginning of the 21st century to jointly open up a new chapter
of cooperation in the Asia-Pacific," he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia will host the meeting next year. APEC meetings
include those of senior officials, trade and foreign ministers and
leaders of the 18 members.
</P>
<P>
APEC, which was initiated in 1989, now groups Australia,
Brunei, Canada, Chile, China, Hong Kong of China, Indonesia,
Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea,
Philippines, Singapore, Chinese Taipei, Thailand and the United
States. 
</P>
