<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Baogang Steel Gets High S&AMP;P Rating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 22 (Xinhua) -- Standard &AMP; Poor has given the
Baoshan Steel Works Group (Baogang), one of China's top steel
works, a triple B-plus debt rating.
</P>
<P>
The rating is identical to China's sovereignty rating and is
the first given by Standard &AMP; Poor to a state-owned enterprise in
China that is not in the financial sector. The high rating will
help the company raise funds on the international capital market.
</P>
<P>
The triple B-plus rating is an indication of Baogang's good
management and sound financial standing, according to a senior
executive at JP Morgan, the steel works' advisor on rating affairs.
</P>
<P>
No other steelworks in the world have been reportedly given a
sovereignty-level debt rating.  
</P>
</TEXT>
