<HEADLINE> Slutskaya Takes Ladies' Singles Title in Cup of Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Irina Slutskaya won ladies'
singles champion in the Cup of Russia Champions Series figure
skating competition Friday in St. Petersburg, Russia, despite a
falling in her free dance.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old double European champion danced in a typical
Russian folk tune and her elegant performances received wild
applause from the Russian spectators.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth victory in the International Skating Union's
Champion Series for the Russian.
</P>
<P>
Russians swept the 1-2-3 finish with Elena Sokolova second and
Olga Markova winning the bronze, besides the gold-medalist.
</P>
<P>
The Russians also took the first-two in pairs event with
Canadians third.
</P>
<P>
Marina Eltsova and Andrei Bushkov, world champions in 1996 and
European title-holders this year, clinched the gold in Ronan
Hardiman's "Lord of the Dance".
</P>
<P>
Evgenia Shishkova and Vadim Naumov took the silver and
Canadians marie-claude Savard-Gagnon and Luc Bradet third.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Angelika Krylova and Oleg Ovsiannikov currently led
the ice dancing event with the first place from Thursday's
compulsories and original dance on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Irina Lobacheva and Ilya Averbukh of Russia followed in the
second place with Tatiana Navka and Nikolai Morozov of Belarus
third.
</P>
<P>
Next meeting of the Champions Series, the last major
international competition before the 1998 Olympics, will be at
Nagano, Japan on November 27-30, with the final held at Munich,
Germany, December 19-21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
