<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Criminal Cases Decrease in Russia: Interior Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Just over two million criminal
cases were reported in Russia between January-October this year,
nine percent lower than the same period last year, Deputy Prime
Minister and Interior Minister Anatoly Kulikov said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
This reduction in crime has occurred in most regions of the
country, Kulikov said, adding that the rate of murder and serious
wounding cases has gone down by two and 15 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Robbery cases have also decreased by seven percent and 118
cases of murder-for-hire have been solved, which is more than
three times the number last year, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
However, Kulikov said, it was too early to say if this trend
can be reversed.
</P>
<P>
Next year, the Russian government will attempt to crack down on
organized and economic crimes, especially those in the financial
field, Kulikov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
