<HEADLINE> China's Textile Production Increases Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from
State Statistical Bureau show that China's textile production
maintained a quick increase during the January-September period
this year.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 3.9 million tons of yarn in the first nine
months this year, up 8.8 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of cloth stood at 15 billion meters, up 11.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of knitting wool was 315,900 tons, up 8.9 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
