<HEADLINE> Output of Major Light Industrial Products in Mixed Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from
State Statistical Bureau show that the output of major light
industrial products changed mixedly during the first months of
1997.
</P>
<P>
During the January-September period, the country made 20.9
million bicycles, down 10.5 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the output of color televisions stood at 17.5
million sets, up 9.9 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
China also manufactured nine million household washing
machines, up 17.7 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
