<HEADLINE> China's Food Production on Steady Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- The output of major food
products registered a stable increase during the first nine months
this year, according to the latest statistics from State
Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the January-September period, China produced 4.7 million
tons of sugar, up 12.1 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of salt reached 21.7 million tons, up 7.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of beer was 15.9 million tons, up 14.9 percent. 
