<HEADLINE> China's Energy Output Increases Stably </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 22 (Xinhua) -- China's energy output reached
934.7 million tons of standard coal during the first nine months
this year, up 2.2 percent on an annual basis, according to the
latest statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the January-September period, China generated one billion
tons of coal, up 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of crude oil hit 121.6 million tons, up 2.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of natural gas was 17.9 billion cubic meters, up 8.5
percent. 
