<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonn Wants "Substantial Dialogue" With Teheran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Germany said today that it hopes
to resume dialogue with Iran after the return of its ambassador to
Tehran on Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Bonn wanted "substantial dialogue" which did not exclude
controversial issues, Martin Erdmann, spokesman for the German
foreign ministry, said today in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
Germany, along with other European Union (EU) states, recalled
their envoys from Teheran in April after a Berlin court ruled that
Iranian leaders ordered the 1992 killings of four Kurdish
dissidents in a Berlin restaurant.
</P>
<P>
Ending a seven-month diplomatic dispute, the EU reached a
compromise with Iran earlier this month to allow their envoys to
return in two groups, with the German and French ambassadors to
come back in the second group. Iran insisted earlier that the
German envoy be the last one to resume his post.
</P>
<P>
After the return of most of EU envoys last Friday, the German
and French ambassadors are due to leave for Teheran on Friday
evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
