<HEADLINE> Four Parties Agree on Formal Talks on Korean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 21 (Xinhua) -- China, the United States, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South Korea today
agreed to hold formal talks on peace on the Korean Peninsula, U.S.
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The accord was reached during the four-party meeting of senior
officials in the campus of Columbia University in New York, which
began earlier in the day. The meeting was the third one in four
months.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the four parties will start the formal
negotiations in Geneva in December. 
</P>
