<HEADLINE> Four-Party Talks on Korea Peninsula to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The United States,
China, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South
Korea have agreed to hold "primary talks" in Geneva next month to
achieve a lasting and stable peace in Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright in Vancouver after his meeting with Canadian foreign
minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
