<HEADLINE> UK Travel Group Cancels Trips to Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 21 (Xinhua) -- One of Britain's top tour
agencies today canceled all holiday trips to Egypt until the end
of the year following a terrible massacre in upper Egypt Monday in
which 59 foreign tourists were killed.
</P>
<P>
"After careful monitoring of the situation in Egypt, Thomson
has decided to cancel all holidays there until Christmas," said a
spokesman of the Thomson tour firm.
</P>
<P>
"We will review the situation before making a decision on
whether or not to operate holidays there during the early part of
1998," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the massacre six Britons and 53 other tourists were shot
dead by six Egyptian fundamentalists at Luxor's Hatshepsut temple,
dealing a heavy blow to the country's thriving tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
He said about 8,000 British holiday makers would be affected
and these people would be offered alternative destinations.
</P>
</TEXT>
